Redesign Phase 2: Send screen — the flagship flow

- Checkbox list -> selectable card grid (GroupSelectCard), with search,
  sort-by-member-count, favorites and per-group tags. Favorites/recent/
  tags are localStorage-only (no backend field exists for them, and
  adding one is out of scope for this UI-only redesign).
- SendTab's draft state (groups/message/image/selection) moved into
  useDashboardStore so the Inspector can read it too.
- SendInspector replaced entirely: it was static/fake before (hardcoded
  "선택된 그룹: 없음", a Toggle wired to nothing). Now shows a real
  live-updating message preview, a real send summary sourced from the
  actual selection, real per-account stats (todaySent/groupCount, both
  already-existing API fields), and a safety-settings panel that states
  the real server-enforced limits instead of a fake toggle.
- Send button is now a floating pill-shaped primary action (sticky to
  the bottom of the scroll area, spring-animated in once the form is
  valid) instead of sitting at the bottom of the form.
- No changes to createBroadcast, fetchGroups, fetchLogs, or any
  send/schedule/rate-limit logic.
